- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 10 blocks arranged in two distinct parts. The left part has 3 blocks, and the right part has 7 blocks. Both parts have a height of 2 layers.
- **Spatial Relationships:**

  - The right part is more complex:
    - Two red arch blocks are positioned side by side at the bottom.
    - A yellow rectangular block spans horizontally across the middle of these arches.
    - On top of this horizontal block, there is another red arch block.
    - To the right of the top arch block, there is a small yellow rectangular block.
